{"id": "ship-plugin-version", "title": "Ship a hansard plugin version (marketplace repo push)", "when": "any plugin code change needs to reach the live install / autoUpdate", "how": "git fetch origin; branch OFF origin/master (local clone is often stale; re-apply net changes, don't rebase a tangled branch); diff live cache vs source FIRST and port any cache-only edits (they die at bumps); bump trainlint/.claude-plugin/plugin.json and verify the bump commit actually touches plugin.json; run tests; git push origin <branch>:master; autoUpdate pulls into a new cache dir (data is safe in data_root/.hansard). Re-check HEAD/version right before bump+push — concurrent sessions move HEAD.", "match": ["ship", "deploy", "release", "bump", "version", "plugin update", "push master", "发布", "部署", "升级"], "source": "/home/shiyil/.claude/projects/-home-shiyil-Trainlint/memory/trainlint-deploy-cache-data.md"}
{"id": "deploy-report-worker", "title": "Deploy the Cloudflare report worker (4 traps)", "when": "report-server/worker/* changed — worker is NOT auto-deployed, commit ≠ live", "how": "1) cp -r the worker dir OUTSIDE the repo (wrangler 4.86 doubles the path inside the git repo) and deploy from the copy; 2) eval \"$(grep '^export CLOUDFLARE' ~/.bashrc)\" and export CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=831dd43403448e005f31bf2b31fc1197; 3) wrangler deploy UPLOADS but route-permission error ABORTS promotion — always follow with `wrangler versions list` then `wrangler versions deploy <id>@100% -y`; 4) wrangler.toml name MUST stay trainlint-report-server (renaming creates an empty second worker with a new DO and no domain). Verify via local.sh miniflare first (pre-prod verifier).", "match": ["worker", "wrangler", "cloudflare", "deploy worker", "secondfoundationlabs", "relay", "report-server"], "source": "/home/shiyil/.claude/projects/-home-shiyil-Trainlint/memory/trainlint-deploy-cache-data.md"}
{"id": "restart-report-daemons", "title": "Restart chat_backend/relay daemons after a code change", "when": "backend/relay code changed and the live report buttons should pick it up", "how": "pkill -f the old-version chat_backend.py and relay_agent.py, then run data_root/keepalive.sh AS ITS OWN command (compound pkill+subshell/`/dev/tcp` commands exit 144 mid-script); keepalive respawns all daemons from the highest-version cache (cron re-runs it every minute). Remote-relay guard is pgrep -f 'relay_agent.py run$' — the $ matters or the local instance satisfies it.", "match": ["restart", "daemon", "keepalive", "chat_backend", "relay_agent", "backend", "重启"], "source": "/home/shiyil/.claude/projects/-home-shiyil-Trainlint/memory/report-feedback-loop.md"}
{"id": "anchor-built-decision", "title": "Anchor a BUILT plan decision to code", "when": "the moment a decision gets an `artifact` — gate G bounces new unanchored builds", "how": "python3 $CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT/research/anchor.py <project> <decision-id> <file>:<start>-<end> (repeatable; --commit <sha>; --paper only for artifact-less decisions, never satisfies a BUILT one). Anchors pin HEAD and refuse ranges that don't exist at HEAD — commit first. viz.py bakes the snippet + drift diff into the report.", "match": ["anchor", "artifact", "built", "pin", "evidence", "file:line", "锚"], "source": "/home/shiyil/.claude/projects/-home-shiyil-Trainlint/memory/anchors-review-evidence.md"}
{"id": "spawn-readonly-claude-agent", "title": "Spawn an airtight read-only headless claude agent", "when": "board/digest investigator agents, or any agent that must not be able to write", "how": "claude -p --output-format stream-json --allowedTools \"Read Grep Glob\" --disallowedTools \"Bash Write Edit NotebookEdit\" --add-dir <data_root> --add-dir <repo_root>. NON-OBVIOUS: --allowedTools alone does NOT remove Bash (read-only shell is auto-approved and Bash can write) — the --disallowedTools list is what makes it airtight. Never --dangerously-skip-permissions.", "match": ["read-only", "readonly", "agent", "claude -p", "headless", "investigator", "spawn", "只读"], "source": "/home/shiyil/.claude/projects/-home-shiyil-Trainlint/memory/report-feedback-loop.md"}
{"id": "kimi-prose-recipe", "title": "Render human-facing prose via kimi CLI", "when": "ANY reader-facing text: report/slides/chat/digest prose, skill/memory/glossary plain fields", "how": "kimi --print -y --output-format stream-json -p '<prompt>'. Standing split: kimi renders for humans, claude/codex do the work (read code, judge, pick ids/keywords) — claude never writes reader-facing prose. Swappable entry is viz._llm(provider,…); env override order HANSARD_REPORT_LLM then TRAINLINT_REPORT_LLM.", "match": ["kimi", "prose", "render", "human-facing", "report text", "人话", "文案"], "source": "/home/shiyil/.claude/projects/-home-shiyil-Trainlint/memory/llm-split-kimi-renders-claude-works.md"}
{"id": "admin-headless-verify", "title": "Verify the live worker as owner/admin from the shell", "when": "need to check the deployed report/admin dashboard headless", "how": "curl -H \"Cookie: trainlint_token=$(cat data_root/.token)\" https://secondfoundationlabs.com/ — the machine token authenticates as voidrank@gmail.com (in ADMIN_EMAILS). Owner-gated routes (digest/resolve/task) have NO admin bypass — test from your OWN ns (flat /<proj>.html or /r/<sha256(email)>/). A bare text 404 from a page button = worker relay route missing; backend 404s are JSON.", "match": ["admin", "verify worker", "curl", "token", "dashboard", "owner", "403", "404"], "source": "/home/shiyil/.claude/projects/-home-shiyil-Trainlint/memory/trainlint-deploy-cache-data.md"}
{"id": "local-worker-preprod", "title": "Run the exact prod worker locally (pre-prod verifier)", "when": "before any prod worker deploy, or to test page buttons off-line", "how": "report-server/local.sh runs the prod worker via wrangler dev --local (miniflare): R2/DO persist under data_root/worker-local, secrets auto-gen into gitignored .dev.vars, binds 0.0.0.0:8787. push.py mirrors reports to it (HANSARD_LOCAL_REPORT_SERVER, 'none' opts out); a second relay instance (`relay_agent.py run local`, own flock) dials it. It caught the getSessCookie infinite recursion before prod — use it every time.", "match": ["local worker", "miniflare", "wrangler dev", "preprod", "8787", "local.sh"], "source": "/home/shiyil/.claude/projects/-home-shiyil-Trainlint/memory/trainlint-deploy-cache-data.md"}
{"id": "add-principle-via-adapter", "title": "Add a project principle WITHOUT forking the rule bank", "when": "about to author a new principle/quiz row for a project", "how": "rules 只有一份: check research/principles.jsonl + quiz.jsonl for a canonical entry covering the law; if covered, add a mapping in research/principle_adapter.json (project-local id → canonical id) — plan.canonical_principle() resolves through it. Only promote a genuinely NEW and transferable law into the bank, once. Never hard-code a project noun into a rule body; the project string goes in project.<name>.json facts.", "match": ["principle", "rule", "quiz", "adapter", "canonical", "principles.jsonl", "规则"], "source": "/home/shiyil/.claude/projects/-home-shiyil-Trainlint/memory/rules-single-source-adapters.md"}
